Purpose of "use strict" is that javascript code should be executed in strict mode.
The scope of "use strict" is global.
"use strict" --> varible should be declared
IE 9 and lower version not support "use strict"
The "use strict" directive was new in ECMAScript version 5.

Example :->

Example of without declare variable

"use strict"; test=2; console.log("Hi..", test);

Output ===> VM754:1 Uncaught ReferenceError: test is not defined
    at <anonymous>:1:19
    
Example :-  declared variable with var keyword
    
"use strict"; var test=2; console.log("Hi..", test);
    
Output ===>    Hi.. 2

Example with function

"use strict"; f= 5; function add(){ console.log("Hi..", (5+f));

Output ===>UVM1034:1 Uncaught ReferenceError: f is not defined

Example with function after declare variable

"use strict"; var f= 5; function add(){ console.log("Hi..", (5+f))};

add()

Output ===> Hi.. 10

Example with same name parameter

"use strict"; function add(p1, p1){ console.log("Hi..", (p1+p1))};

Output ===> Uncaught SyntaxError: Duplicate parameter name not allowed in this context



   
